text: what advice would you give to your young
self or young people in general who want
to get involved in comedy and do what
you guys do yeah don't be afraid to fail
like if people don't understand what
you're doing right away I would say look
for collaborative collaborators and like
people understand your sensibility and
people who you feel like you can grow
around and take chances with and then
that don't compare yourself is like a
huge one because I feel like that
gets in the way so quickly and
especially like if you're just like one
of two women in like your local scene or
whatever people are automatically gonna
like pit you against each other for no
reason and it's just not necessary and
and I think that there's also a quote I
once heard with about comparing people
where it's like we always compare other
people's highlight reels to our behind
the scenes so it's like we you know it's
like all of our process and failure we
compared to other people's like best
moments and it's like it's never gonna
pan out in your favor so yeah yes
loyalty counts in this industry and I
think that like if you can find your
people you know it's easy to be jealous
it's easy to compete it's easy to fall
apart but like find the good loyal
people and like fight for them and fight
for yourself
